         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>Marcia C<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
               <lb n="2"/> vixit <expan><abbr>ann</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
               <hi rend="supraline">
                  <num>
                     <unclear>XV</unclear>
                  </num>
               </hi>
               <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
               <lb n="3"/> Ultima <unclear>i</unclear>
               <supplied reason="lost">am subii crudeli fun</supplied>
               <lb n="4" break="no"/>ere <unclear>f</unclear>
               <supplied reason="lost">ata</supplied>
               <lb n="5"/> et nunc angus<supplied reason="lost">to comprimor</supplied>
               <lb n="6"/> in lapide.
                <lb n="7"/> Quid queror infelix <supplied reason="lost">non</supplied>
               <lb n="8"/> responsura s<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">orori</supplied>?
            </ab>
            <!-- The marked up transcription goes here, surrounded by <ab> </ab> elements -->
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Marcia [-] lived for [X] years.</p>
            <p>Already, I have submitted to the ultimate
               fate, merciless death, and now I am contained in (this) narrow gravestone. Why do I,
               unhappy (and) unable to attend to (my) sister, lament?</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 1: the deceased's cognomen, beginning with a "C," is missing.</p>
            <p>Line 2: VIX ANN X V (CIL). The numeral indicating the number of years the deceased lived may be incomplete; it is at least fifteen. The number of months and days she lived may also be missing.</p>
            <p>Lines 3-4: ultima f[ata subi lugenti]/ erep[ta marito]. Line 8: [sodali] (Sheldon in Boldwin and Torelli, CLE)</p>
         </div>
